MANUEL LOPEZ MARTINEZ TEJADA (28),
PLEADED GUILTY ,
for that he, in incurring a liability amounting to 20,000l. unlawfully did obtain credit by fraud and false pretences;
also failing to discover to the trustee administering his estate all his property;
also to embezzling an order for the payment of 461l. 11s. 5d., the property of
His Majesty the King of Spain;
also to stealing divers Spanish Bonds, for the payment of 443, 105l., and 121 orders for the payment of 1,851l. 6s. the property of
His Majesty the King of Spain.
Recommended to mercy by the Prosecutor—Judgment respited . (See Half-yearly Index.) And
